- Getting started
Start from your own version of roc-lab2, or get it from the repo:
 git clone git://github.com/kudelabs/roc-lab2.git

$ rake db:migrate

- create User model, add relations to Messsages and Replies.

$ rails generate model users name:string email:string  password:string
in user model, add
has_many :messages
has_many :replies

add to messages and replies: belongs_to :user



+ check reply migration
+ check reply.rb - see belongs_to

+ add :has_many relation to messages

$ rake db:migrate

- test drive the new model

$ rails console
>msg = Message.new(:body=>"I am from the command line")
>msg.save
>Message.create(:body=>"This does an insert")
>msg.replies.create(:body=>'Really?')
>r = msg.replies.build(:body=>"Yes, it does!")
>r.save
>msg = Message.find(2)
>msg.replies.collect(&:body)

+ add nested replies resource to routes.rb  

$ rails s

- edit messages#show
